<p> </p>

<p>We merged the antibacterial properties of gold with the natural whitening and absorbing powers of bamboo charcoal. The result is a toothbrush your teeth will thank you for!</p>

<p> </p>

<p>IT'S 2016, WHY BRUSH WITH A 77 YEARS OLD TOOTHBRUSH?</p>

<p> </p>

<p>Most toothbrush bristles are made of nylon or nylon-polyester. That’s it! It’s pretty much the same material DuPont first used in 1938. In a way that’s fine, because nylon and polyester are actually a pretty good options, but it’s 2015 and there sure needs to be a way to improve the bristles' material.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>ANTIBACTERIAL GOLD TOOTHBRUSH</p>

<p> </p>

<p>Pretty much all toothbrushes are covered with millions of bacteria. Mythbusters have found it, studies  have found it, it’s a fact. It’s really weird nothing was done about this for so long, when this concerns something we put in our mouths twice a day, every day.</p>

<p> </p>

<p> </p>

As a result, half of Nano-b Charcoal and Gold bristles are impregnated with genuine gold nano-particles. Once on your toothbrush, gold works its magic.</p>

<p> </p>
